<div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Romhacking *is* perfectly legal, however, claiming any copyright on it is not.<br /></div><br />Er no, it's not legal. It creates a derivative work, and unless you have been given permission, that's not legal (although ironically, as mentioned above, you get copyright over the modified parts, effectively giving two copyright owners to the hack). Mind you, the copy originally used for making the hack in itself was probably infringement in the first place =P<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4526">Sik</a> — Sun Jan 04, 2015 4:40 pm</p><hr />
